title: Cibulka
text: Cibulka (feminine Cibulková) is a widespread name in the former Czechoslovakia as well as throughout the former Austro-Hungarian Empire, where it was frequently spelt Czibulka according to the <a href="List%20of%20Latin%20digraphs%23C">older Hungarian orthography</a>. It may originate from a diminutive of the Czech word cibule, meaning "onion."
